items.title: JPMorgan Chase & Co. (JPM) Laps the Stock Market: Here's Why
items.description: JPMorgan Chase & Co. (JPM) reached $278.27 at the closing of the latest trading day, reflecting a +1.19% change compared to its last close.

items.title: Big banks are close to getting one of biggest regulatory rollbacks since 2008
items.description: US regulators this week are expected to weigh one of the most dramatic rollbacks of bank capital rules since the 2008 financial crisis, which would give a major victory to lenders seeking relief from the new Trump administration.

items.title: Young Investor Demand for Alternative Assets Is Reshaping Wall Street's Playbook
items.description: (Bloomberg) -- Wall Street has a new favorite investor. They’re young, they’re affluent and they’re skeptical that traditional markets can deliver wealth over the long haul.
